content.text:
Let me analyze the target image and provide instructions for building both structures.

Main Target Image Analysis:
The image shows two separate structures:

Structure 1 (Left) - "Tower on Wheels":
- 5 layers total
- Base: Two orange cylindrical blocks (wheels)
- Green rectangular block above wheels
- Red cube block
- Blue cube block
- Orange triangular roof piece

Structure 2 (Right) - "House":
- 4 layers of blocks arranged in a house shape
- Base: 2x2 arrangement of orange and blue cubes
- Green rectangular block horizontally placed
- Orange triangular roof piece

Block Selection and Assembly Instructions:

For Structure 1 (Tower on Wheels):
{
    Step1: Move block with index 10 (orange cylinder - left wheel)
    Step2: Move block with index 10 (orange cylinder - right wheel)
    Step3: Move block with index 7 (green rectangular block)
    Step4: Move block with index 4 (red cube)
    Step5: Move block with index 1 (blue cube)
    Step6: Move block with index 12 (orange triangular roof)
}

For Structure 2 (House):
{
    Step1: Move block with index 3 (orange cube)
    Step2: Move block with index 1 (blue cube)
    Step3: Move block with index 1 (blue cube)
    Step4: Move block with index 3 (orange cube)
    Step5: Move block with index 7 (green rectangular block)
    Step6: Move block with index 12 (orange triangular roof)
}
